10 Things to Remember as a Bride’s Sister 👩‍❤️‍💋‍👩

	1.	You’re not the bride, but you are the second lead. Dress accordingly. 😌
	2.	Touch-up kit = lifeline. Keep mini lipstick, compact, pins, tissues. Always.
	3.	You’re in every photo. Don’t let your eyeliner betray you.
	4.	Reel pe reel banwa lo… yeh moment dobara nahi aayega! 💃📸
	5.	Don’t cry too much – waterproof mascara has its limits. 😭
	6.	Blouse fitting > emotional breakdown. Get it trialed early.
	7.	That ‘simple makeup look’ you wanted? It’ll turn full glam. Just go with it. ✨
	8.	Start saving 6 months early. Between outfits, gifts, and facials – you’re broke but glowing. 💸
	9.	Hair open? Hair tied? You’ll change it 5 times before the baraat. 🤦‍♀️
	10.	People will ask “tumhari shaadi kab hai?” at least 17 times. SMILE THROUGH IT. 😅
